{
  "article_id": "ThePeeDeeBee1879",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "The "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Francisco journals",
        "entity_key": "sfchronicle",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "contain an account of what they call a "
      },
      {
        "text": "Californian Crusoe",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "an Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who had for eighteen years lived alone on "
      },
      {
        "text": "a dreary desert island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and was finally discovered and taken off by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the crew",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of "
      },
      {
        "text": "a vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "in search of her. Many years ago "
      },
      {
        "text": "a small schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "was sent to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "island of San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Pacific",
        "entity_key": "re_pacific",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", some seventy-five miles southeast of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", to bring away "
      },
      {
        "text": "a number of Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "living there and settle them on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the main land",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nineteen men, women and children",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been got on board, when one of them, "
      },
      {
        "text": "a mother",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", found that "
      },
      {
        "text": "two of her offspring",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been left behind. "
      },
      {
        "text": "She immediately jumped overboard and swam to ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where she sought in vain for ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her children",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Having returned to the shore, she saw "
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "sailing away, and tried in vain to attract attention. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was not visited again for sixteen years. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Then ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "George Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", an otter-hunter, commanding ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a small vessel",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", landed there, and detected evidences of human habitation, but could not stay long enough [to prosecute his quest. Two years after he sailed there again, and, roaming over] ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", came upon ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who was not at all wild, and made no effort to escape.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She was clad in a garment fashioned of the skin of a sea-fowl, and was occupied in skinning seal-blubber, which had formed the greater part of her diet. She was quite good-looking, seemed about fifty years old, and spoke a language nobody could understand. She died a few weeks after reaching "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", while living in the "
      },
      {
        "text": "house of Nidever",
        "entity_key": "nideverhouse",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", from the effects of a fall seriously injuring her spine."
      }
    ]
  ]
}